post_text:
Happy Labor Day,

This is a reminder that currently, our K-8 classes on campus are held primarily outside and will be canceled for inclement weather (thunderstorms, heavy rain, high winds). We will try to make the call by 7:00 AM based on The Weather Channel forecast for the hours of 12 - 3 (voice announcements will be sent via One Call Now and it will be posted at https://www.facebook.com/RenaissanceAcad) but if storms blow in after that, for the safety of our students and staff, classes will be canceled and the remainder of school for the day will be virtual.

On virtual only days, there will be small group and individual meetings with students in the afternoon as well as an end of day meeting at 2:30 PM for Kindergarten through grade 3, and 3 o'clock for grades 4 to 8.

Thankfully, as of right now, the forecast is looking good for Tuesday afternoon. We hope to see everyone at school tomorrow. Enjoy the rest of your holiday!

On virtual only days, there will be small group and individual meetings with students in the afternoon as well as an end of day meeting at 2:30 PM for Kindergarten through grade 3, and 3 o'clock for grades 4 to 8.

I‚Äôm sure this pandemic isn‚Äôt how you imagined your graduation day would be.

You must know you left 6th grade footprints on my heart.

Congratulations to the class of 2020

The Kindergartners heard the story of the "Little Red Hen" last week. Since the Little Red Hen made bread in the story, two videos showing how some breads are made was shared in our Google Classroom. One video showed people making Navajo Fry Bread.
So on April 21st, Emma and her mom, Amanda, made traditional Navajo fry bread. They mixed the ingredients and cooked the flatbread in oil. Once it was finished and cooled, they added taco toppings. Delicious!

Many children (and adults too) struggle to be in touch with and express their feelings. Too often children are not allowed their feelings because adults try to fix, squelch or even deny feelings. Instead, it is much more helpful to just validate feelings. You can do this by asking a simple question or reflecting back with empathy.
#positivediscipline #positivedisciplinetoolcards
Read the articles below for helpful tips on validating children's feelings.
https://www.positivediscipline.com/articles/validate-feelings-positive-discipline-tool-card

post_text:
Trouble with Fast ForWord on your child's iPad?

Recent updates to iOS 13.x have caused conflicts with some Scientific Learning programs on iPad.

The symptom: A student will open one of the assignments mentioned above in the Safari browser. The exercise selector screen will appear, displaying the icons for the day's scheduled exercises. At this point tapping on any of the exercise icons does not produce a response.

Resolution: To resolve the issue in Safari, take the following steps:
1. Go to Settings >> Safari >>Request Desktop Website >>All Websites
2. Change the All Websites setting to ‚ÄúOFF‚Äù

Another workaround for the issue is to use the Chrome browser in iPad.
text:
Trouble with Fast ForWord on your child's iPad?

Recent updates to iOS 13.x have caused conflicts with some Scientific Learning programs on iPad.

The symptom: A student will open one of the assignments mentioned above in the Safari browser. The exercise selector screen will appear, displaying the icons for the day's scheduled exercises. At this point tapping on any of the exercise icons does not produce a response.

Resolution: To resolve the issue in Safari, take the following steps:
1. Go to Settings >> Safari >>Request Desktop Website >>All Websites
2. Change the All Websites setting to ‚ÄúOFF‚Äù

Another workaround for the issue is to use the Chrome browser in iPad.

From Erik Tannehill, Soup Kitchen Coordinator in Michigan City:

After contacting all of Michigan City representatives and ministry leaders from our soup kitchens/community meals, we have a finalized schedule to share. This is effective until further notice:

Sunday-Thursday, Saturday (12 Noon - 1 PM) First United Methodist Church parking lot, On 7th St near Franklin St. in MIchigan City

Friday (11:30 AM - 1:00 PM) Macedonia Baptist Church, 3007 Ohio St. in Michigan City

Please let others know about this program, especially in these trying times.

One meal per person please. If you have a family or anyone homebound and need a constant supply of meals, please contact me personally at cheferiktannehill@gmail.com

Please share widely as we will take care of anyone who could use a meal.

Thank you to all of the volunteers, churches and donors who are keeping this program supported in this time of need.

Chef Erik and the Mighty Community Sous Chefs

post_text: Truth.
shared_text:
Ken Buck
March 18 at 8:47 AM ¬∑

We gave educators almost no notice. We asked them to completely redesign what school looks like and in about 24 hours local administrators and teachers "Apollo 13'ed" the problem and fixed it. Kids learning, children being fed, needs being met in the midst of a global crisis.
No state agency did this, no so-called national experts on curriculum. The local educators fixed it in hours. HOURS.
In fact, existing state and federal policies actually created multiple roadblocks. Local schools figured out how to do it around those too. No complaining and no handwringing - just solutions and amazingly clever plans.
Remember that the next time someone tries to convince you that schools are better run by mandates from non-educators. Remember that the next time someone tells you that teachers have it easy or try to persuade you that educators are not among the smartest, most ingenious people in society. And please never say to me again, "Those who can't do anything else just go into teaching."
Get out of the way of a teacher and watch with amazement at what really happens.

post_text:
How neat is this??!

If you go to the website below, you get a google-earth like globe that you can spin, and it shows zillions of radio station feeds from all over the world. You can zoom in or out, and if you center the white circle on a green dot (representing a station) you can hear what they're playing. I've already listened to Nanoq FM in Greenland, some Icelandic madness, and two stations in County Donegal. They have great music! You can go to any part of the world!

If you move the circle off the green dot, you lose the feed.

http://radio.garden/

post_text:
Good Morning Renaissance Families!

Due to the severe weather and poor road conditions, area schools are closed. As on all Snow Days, students should complete one day of the Home/Snow/e Learning packet that was sent home this fall. That means a reading assignment or home reading, a math work, and writing an essay.

Friday's Annual Ski Day/Home Learning school day is still on - winter weather won't stop that!

Parent-Teacher Conferences scheduled for today will be moved to the same times next week on Thursday, February 20, which will be a half day of school. If you need to reschedule your conference, please let your child's teacher know on Tuesday so we can adjust your time.

We understand many students were very excited about Valentine's, so Valentine exchanges will still take place next week by class when it fits best in their schedules. Elementary students should bring their Valentine's on Tuesday to be stored until their class exchange. Preschool/Kindergarten will celebrate on Wednesday.

Hope you can enjoy an unexpected extra long weekend!

post_text:
Dear Families,

A significant number of students were absent and were sent home sick from school today. We are aware of a number of highly contagious illnesses in the area: Influenza A, Influenza B, Strep, and Viral Gastroenteritis (often referred to as the "stomach flu"). Symptoms kids are being sent home for are fevers, nausea and/or vomiting. Headache, sore throat, and/or not feeling well are additional symptoms being reported.

Please remember, any child home sick should not return until they are clear of symptoms for at least 24 hours without the use of medications, unless under the communication of a physician.

Thank you for helping R school community as healthy as possible.
